        <num>CC 1405</num>
        <heading>1405.  Sale of succession rights to coheir at risk of vendor, rescission inadmissible</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1405.  Sale of succession rights to coheir at risk of vendor, rescission inadmissible.
The sale of successive rights by one heir to his coheir is not subject * to rescission, if the purchaser has run no risk; as, for example, if the vendor remains bound for the payment of the debts.
* Note error in English translation of French text; &quot;is not subject&quot; should be &quot;is subject.&quot;</p>
        </content>
